Caption from <i><a href="http://cas.awm.gov.au/photograph/E00833">AWM:</a></i>

&quot;Supporting troops of the 1st Australian Division walking on a duckboard track near Hooge, in the Ypres Sector. They form a silhouettte against the sky as they pass towards the front line to relieve their comrades, whose attack the day before won Broodseinde Ridge and deepened the Australian advance.

Taken October 5, 1917, at Western Front (Belgium), Menin Road Area, Hooge.&quot;
